-- Singapore's DBS agrees to buy SocGen's Asian private bank -sources
-- By Saeed Azhar
-- Fri Mar 14, 2014 08:06AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, March 14 (Reuters) - Singapore's DBS Group Holdings Ltd <DBSM.SI> has agreed to buy French bank Societe Generale's (SocGen) <SOGN.PA> Asian private bank for about $250 million, people familiar with the matter told Reuters on Friday.

A deal is expected to be announced as early as Monday, said the sources, who declined to be identified as the information is not public.